******
[1] Bulgaria
Date: Fri 27 May 2016
Source: News.bg (Bulgaria) [in Bulgarian, mach. trans., edited]
https://news.bg/economics/oshte-100-000-vaksini-za-zhivotnite-v-yuzhna-balgariya-pristigat-do-kraya-na-mesetsa.html


Another 100 000 [doses of lumpy skin disease (LSD)] vaccines for animals arrive in southern Bulgaria by the end of the month [May 2016].

The 2nd batch of 175 000 doses of vaccines against [LSD] have almost been fully applied.

At today's [27 May 2016] meeting in the Ministry of Agriculture and Food, dealing with the said issue, it has become clear that the 3rd consignment of 100 000 [doses] of the vaccine will arrive earlier than expected, namely next week and not at the end of June. This will allow the immunisation of all susceptible animals in southern Bulgaria.

LSD infection in cattle has not yet been overcome; new outbreaks are reported every day. They are currently still in southern and western Bulgaria, but measures to control and limit introduction in the north of the country are being undertaken.

The meeting confirmed backing Bulgaria's efforts in obtaining the European Commission's agreement to apply the required effective measures to reduce and eradicate LSD, minimizing losses to [Bulgarian] farmers and the Member States.

The Ministry has received the support of the veterinary scientific community who have promised to draft an opinion to support their country before the European Commission.

Recall last week Bulgaria asked the European Commission to come up with a special decision on measures to tackle lumpy skin disease. The request for debate by Minister Desislava Taneva was supported by [Vytenis Povilas] Andriukaitis, European Commissioner-designate [responsible for Health and Food Safety].

--
